On Monday, the papers went up slightly.
On Friday, Filip Dierckx, a new CEO, was appointed to head the bank.
The financial institution has also been looking for private customers, but no one has made a substantial offer so far.
The Belgian Government has already indicated that investors do not have to worry or lose their money.
